snippet.textDisplay: Jimmy Kimmel, you are such a class act. Your heartfelt opening was so touching.  The respect that you showed to Kobe and Gianna, as well as the other seven "friends", and mentioning their names, was priceless. I watched Stephen Colbert's touching tribute too where he mentioned all nine victims. Another class act. There are multiple families dealing with the unthinkable loss of their loved ones, and we all grieve for them too. John, Keri and Alyssa Altobelli, Sarah and Peyton Chester, Christina Mauser and Ara Zobayan. May they all rest in peace, dance and play basketball in heaven together. I think I have watched nearly every interview that Kobe Bryant has ever given in these past four days.  I have come to know and love this young man more than I ever could have imagined.  He was so articulate, driven, committed, creative, loving, kind, inspiring, grounded, smart, talented, funny, happy, giving, and just all around fabulous! His love for his wife and four girls was the most precious part of who he was. The world needs more Kobe Bryant's in it. My prayer is that Kobe's passing will help heal humanity's heart and make us all realize that we are ONE big family, feeling the loss like everyone else. And coming together to pray and help lift their loved ones up who are mourning their unimaginable losses. Let me say that again in a different way...Thank you, Kobe, Gianna, John, Keri, Alyssa, Sarah, Peyton, Christina and Ara, for HELPING TO HEAL HUMANITY'S HEART.  You have taught the world invaluable life lessons on living in the moment, telling those you love what they mean to you, forgiving any past indifferences with family and friends because life is fleeting, and not taking one day, one hour, or even one minute for granted. Your legacy will live onward to infinity. If there is any silver lining in this tragedy, which is truly hard to find, is that Kobe and Gianna were probably in each other's arms in those final moments, and in an instant their souls emerged, rising up to heaven together, Dad's arm around his little girl, looking down and wrapping their hearts and spirits around Vanessa, Natalia, Bianka and baby Capri Kobe. I imagine the same thing happened with the other families too. I have visualized all nine of them already playing basketball in heaven. But most importantly, they are all surrounding their loved ones with their spirits and comforting them in their greatest time of need. The enormous outpouring of love that the world is bestowing upon them is the greatest indication of a life well lived.  We should all strive to live our life in such a way that when we transition onward we leave this kind of a legacy.  Keep shining upward and onward all of you lovely souls. Keep a daily watch over your loved ones, until the day comes when you are reunited in heaven. God bless, surround, protect and comfort the families who are grieving, and all those who feel this collective loss. And may we all rise up and shine on. And be kinder to one another. Love is the answer. xoxo Diane Carty

Flight into Terrain by Ed Seaver Vinuesa



If Kobe's leased Sikorsky S-76B helicopter was not equipped with Terrain Awareness and Warning System (TAWS). The National Transportation Safety Board, NTSB, and the The Federal Aviation Administration, FAA, must investigate if the pilot downloaded the TAWS App to his tablet or smartphone.

Lesson: What lesson can we learn from this tragedy? We can use every tool at our disposal to ensure a safe flight especially when we have family and friends on board.

A safety culture is NOT a checklist item! It's a way of operating that pays attention to details.

snippet.textDisplay:
Biden’s daughter:



Ashley Biden organization received $166K federal grant while father was
vice president




A Delaware nonprofit organization
received a $166,000 federal grant about the same time it appointed then-Vice
President Joe Biden’s daughter as executive director, according to government
and tax records.





In September 2014, the Delaware
Center for Justice was selected for a competitive two-year grant by the U.S.
Department of Justice through the federal Edward Byrne Memorial grant program,
which Biden helped steer significant funding to as vice president and senator.





His daughter, Ashley Biden, 38, had
been associate director of the Delaware Center for Justice for about a year at
the time. Two months after the grant selection, the nonprofit organization
announced that she had been promoted to executive director.





Joe Biden was one of the top
advocates for the Edward Byrne grant while in the Senate and helped steer $1.7 billion to the program as vice president. The grant,
which was named in honor of a fallen New York City Police Department officer,
typically supports efforts to strengthen local law enforcement. The program has
also faced criticism from justice reform organizations, including the American
Civil Liberties Union, which claimed it perpetuated “racial disparities, police corruption,
over-incarceration and civil rights abuses.”

snippet.textDisplay: Damn man this one is rough. Sitting home last Sunday about to watch the sorry ass pro bowl then blam breaking news Kobe dies in a helo crash. WHAT no way not Kobe Bryant man. Ive been sick for 4 days now like i lost a long lost brother. As a father of 2 awesome daughters myself i cant even imagine. I despised Kobe Bryant as im from Chicago and was a die hard Bulls fan. I despised the man only because he was the only threat to our Michael Jordan, but i always respected this man as a ball player cause he was a talent we hardly ever see anymore. I can remember where i was when this kid in 96 got drafted. He grew up with us from 17 years to 41 years old. All i wanna say is RIP to a legend and his beautiful daughter. And all his friends on that chopper. Ill never forget watching u and MJ crack jokes on eachother you went to soon with so much yet to give and live. The world still mornes you brother. Bryant family i hope u find peace to heal your broken hearts. Bryant touched so many with his grace on the floor and his larger than life persona!!! Love and respect to all 9. RIP!!!🙏🙏
